{"author":"RebarBotNava","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"alias":"zincoid-panoramic-eeve","creation_channel":"cli","description":"## Summary\nCut the 0.10.1 patch release of rebar per docs/releasing.md. This is a fix/patch bump from 0.10.0, covering the ~36 commits landed on main since v0.10.0 (reconciler Backend-port scalar surfaces, plan-review/close-gate hardening, code-health analyzers: scc/lizard/jscpd, review-bot token accounting, and assorted fixes).\n\n## Plan\n1. Fresh worktree from origin/main.\n2. Bump versions in lockstep: pyproject.toml [project].version, server.json top-level version + every packages[].version -> 0.10.1.\n3. CHANGELOG.md: prepend the [0.10.1] section via 'make changelog VERSION=v0.10.1', hand-curate, add the compare-link footer.\n4. Local gates: make lint && make typecheck && make test; python -m build && twine check.\n5. Commit with rebar-ticket + DCO trailers; push gerrit HEAD:refs/for/main; earn LLM-Review +1 AND Verified +1; Submit.\n6. Fast-forward worktree; dispatch release.yml from main with version=0.10.1 (gh workflow run); approve the pypi deployment when prompted.\n7. Verify PyPI serves 0.10.1; GitHub Release + v0.10.1 tag created; MCP registry + Homebrew autobump follow.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n- 0.10.1 published to PyPI (nava-rebar) with version-lockstep across pyproject/server.json.\n- v0.10.1 tag + GitHub Release created at the released main SHA.\n- Release commit landed on main through Gerrit with both gate votes green.\n- CHANGELOG.md carries a curated [0.10.1] section.","id":"5ac8-96d1-4691-49a5","parent_id":"","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"task","title":"Release 0.10.1 (patch/fix version)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1784861019725927001,"uuid":"b30f28c9-ed26-4f59-ae55-757e48d37c4b"}